This is your first assignment and will be executed individually. From the pile of ideas that your group has brainstormed, choose ONE to flesh out into an Idea Document. Everyone in your group must choose a DIFFERENT idea. The purpose of this assignment is to get you thinking about a game idea as a game designer and to critically and practically apply some of the concepts from Weeks 1 & 2 of the course.

 

Details
You must complete these three components of the Idea Document:

In no more than 1-3 full sentences provide a Vision Statement or “elevator pitch” for your game: what is your game about and what makes it unique? This should be clear, concise, and immediately understandable. Be sure to include which of the 5 Game Profiles it fits.
Using the Game Elements Tetrad that we learned about in Week 1, define the Aesthetics, Mechanics, Story, and Technology for your Game Idea as you envision it today. You should include 2-3 bullet points for each section. You may create this as an image/chart or as text under each section.
Identify 2-4 Player Motivations for your Game Idea using the Player Motivations we learned about in Week 2 and read about in Ishai Smadja’s article hereLinks to an external site.. In 1-2 full sentences for each Motivation, explain why these are motivations for your game’s players. 
