请参考以下内容
The game that I chose is Wordscapes. 

Action

The player uses the letters they are given to spell out all the viable words possible from the given pool of letters.
The tactile experience consists of swiping on the letters so that words can be spelled in one continuous motion. 
They may spend money on hints or to reshuffle the order that the letters are in.
Some levels have challenge words that are not necessary to complete the level, but provide the players with additional coins.
Reward

Completing a level grants the player with points towards a progress meter which rewards the players with coins or powerups after a threshold has been met.
They also gain brilliance points, which is a scoring system that is used to compare the player to other players in their friend list, their nearby area, and globally. 
They also receive flashy feedback letters that congratulate the player on how well they are doing, which creates a sense of accomplishment.
There are rewards for challenge words in the game, but there are also coin bonuses if the player spells out a bonus word that is not included in the puzzle.
Progress

As players complete levels, they gain player experience which provide them with levels. Leveling up creates a sense of accomplishment and provides rewards.
Leveling up also unlocks new features. 
There is also a smaller progress meter which increases by 1 every time a level is completed. The giftbox at the end of the progress meter gives the player gold or powerups.
Players progress through different areas, where color schemes and specific themes are introduced. The difficulty also increases as players move into new areas. 
Long-term progression

Over a long period of time, players eventually build up enough brilliance points to place on leaderboards. This fulfills a competitive aspect to an otherwise non-competitive game that provides players with a sense of accomplishment and pride. 
